---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Privacy Policy" description="ToolMixr privacy policy - your data stays in your browser.">

  <div class="legal-page">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="updated">Last updated: June 9, 2026</p>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>1. Overview</h2>
      <p>ToolMixr ("we", "our", or "us") is committed to protecting your privacy. This policy explains how we collect, use, and protect information when you visit <strong>toolmixr.com</strong>.</p>
      <p>All tools on ToolMixr run <strong>entirely in your browser</strong>. We do not collect, store, or transmit any data you enter into our tools. The text you type, files you process, and results you generate never leave your device.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
      <h3>2.1 Information You Do NOT Provide</h3>
      <p>We do <strong>not</strong> collect any of the following:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Personal identification information (name, email, address)</li>
        <li>Data entered into tools (JSON, text, images, passwords)</li>
        <li>Financial data from calculators (mortgage, ROI, loan data)</li>
        <li>Account credentials or passwords</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>2.2 Automatically Collected Information</h3>
      <p>Like most websites, certain information is automatically collected when you visit:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Usage Data:</strong> Pages visited, time spent on pages, referral sources</li>
        <li><strong>Device Data:</strong> Browser type and version, operating system, screen resolution</li>
        <li><strong>IP Address:</strong> Anonymized IP address for geolocation analytics</li>
      </ul>
      <p>This data is collected through Google Analytics and is aggregated and anonymized. No personally identifiable information is collected through these services.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>3. How We Use Information</h2>
      <p>We use automatically collected data for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Site Analytics:</strong> Understanding which tools and pages are most popular, which helps us improve ToolMixr</li>
        <li><strong>Performance Monitoring:</strong> Identifying and fixing site performance issues</li>
        <li><strong>Advertising:</strong> Serving relevant advertisements through Google AdSense</li>
      </ul>
      <p>We do <strong>not</strong> sell, rent, or share your personal data with third parties for their own marketing purposes.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>4. Cookies</h2>
      <p>ToolMixr uses cookies and similar technologies for the following purposes:</p>

      <h3>4.1 Essential Cookies</h3>
      <p>These cookies are necessary for the website to function properly. They include:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Theme Preference:</strong> Stores your dark/light mode preference (localStorage)</li>
        <li><strong>Cookie Consent:</strong> Remembers your cookie consent choice (localStorage)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>4.2 Analytics Cookies</h3>
      <p><strong>Google Analytics (GA4)</strong> sets cookies to collect anonymized usage statistics:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><code>_ga</code> — Used to distinguish users (expires after 2 years)</li>
        <li><code>_ga_&lt;container-id&gt;</code> — Used to persist session state (expires after 2 years)</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Google Analytics does not collect personally identifiable information. You can learn more at <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

      <h3>4.3 Advertising Cookies</h3>
      <p><strong>Google AdSense</strong> uses cookies to serve personalized ads based on your browsing history:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Third-party vendors, including Google, use cookies to serve ads based on your prior visits to this website or other websites</li>
        <li>Google's use of advertising cookies enables it and its partners to serve ads based on your visit to this site and/or other sites on the Internet</li>
      </ul>
      <p>You can opt out of personalized advertising by visiting <a href="https://www.google.com/settings/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google's Ads Settings</a> or <a href="https://www.aboutads.info/choices/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.aboutads.info</a>.</p>

      <h3>4.4 Managing Cookies</h3>
      <p>You can manage or disable cookies through your browser settings. Most browsers allow you to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>View and delete existing cookies</li>
        <li>Block third-party cookies</li>
        <li>Block all cookies from specific sites</li>
        <li>Browse in private/incognito mode</li>
      </ul>
      <p>Note that disabling cookies may affect the functionality of certain website features.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>5. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>We use the following third-party services that may collect data as described in their respective privacy policies:</p>
      <table class="legal-table">
        <thead>
          <tr><th>Service</th><th>Purpose</th><th>Data Collected</th><th>Privacy Policy</th></tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr>
            <td>Google Analytics (GA4)</td>
            <td>Anonymous traffic analytics</td>
            <td>Page views, session duration, device info</td>
            <td><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Link</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Google AdSense</td>
            <td>Display advertising</td>
            <td>Cookies for ad personalization</td>
            <td><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Link</a></td>
          </tr>
          <tr>
            <td>Cloudflare</td>
            <td>Hosting, CDN, security</td>
            <td>IP address, request metadata</td>
            <td><a href="https://www.cloudflare.com/privacypolicy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Link</a></td>
          </tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>6. Data Retention</h2>
      <p>Automatically collected analytics data is retained by Google Analytics for a maximum of 26 months. We do not independently store or retain any visitor data on our servers.</p>
      <p>Cookie data is stored in your browser and can be cleared at any time through your browser settings.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>7. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>Depending on your jurisdiction, you may have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>

      <h3>7.1 GDPR (European Economic Area & UK)</h3>
      <p>Under the General Data Protection Regulation, you have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Access:</strong> Request a copy of personal data we hold about you</li>
        <li><strong>Rectification:</strong> Request correction of inaccurate personal data</li>
        <li><strong>Erasure:</strong> Request deletion of your personal data ("right to be forgotten")</li>
        <li><strong>Restriction:</strong> Request restriction of processing of your personal data</li>
        <li><strong>Portability:</strong> Request transfer of your data to another service</li>
        <li><strong>Objection:</strong> Object to processing of your personal data</li>
      </ul>
      <p>To exercise any of these rights, contact us at <a href="mailto:contact@toolmixr.com">contact@toolmixr.com</a>.</p>

      <h3>7.2 CCPA (California, USA)</h3>
      <p>Under the California Consumer Privacy Act, California residents have the right to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Know what personal data is being collected</li>
        <li>Know whether their personal data is sold or disclosed and to whom</li>
        <li>Say no to the sale of personal data (we do not sell personal data)</li>
        <li>Access their personal data</li>
        <li>Request deletion of their personal data</li>
        <li>Not be discriminated against for exercising privacy rights</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>8. Children's Privacy</h2>
      <p>ToolMixr is not directed at children under the age of 13 (or 16 in certain EU member states). We do not knowingly collect personal information from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal data, please contact us and we will delete it promptly.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>9. International Data Transfers</h2>
      <p>Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your country of residence. These countries may have data protection laws that differ from your jurisdiction. We take appropriate safeguards to ensure your data remains protected in accordance with this privacy policy.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>10. Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We may update this privacy policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, legal requirements, or operational needs. The "Last updated" date at the top of this page indicates when the most recent changes were made. We encourage you to review this policy periodically.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="legal-section">
      <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>If you have questions, concerns, or requests regarding this privacy policy or your personal data, please contact us at:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:contact@toolmixr.com">contact@toolmixr.com</a></li>
        <li><strong>Website:</strong> <a href="/contact">Contact Form</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p>We will respond to your inquiry within 30 days as required by applicable law.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .legal-page { padding: 40px 0 80px; max-width: 800px; }
  .legal-page h1 { font-size: 32px; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 8px; }
  .legal-page .updated { color: var(--text-secondary); margin-bottom: 40px; font-size: 14px; }
  .legal-section { margin-bottom: 40px; }
  .legal-section h2 { font-size: 22px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 16px; padding-bottom: 8px; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); }
  .legal-section h3 { font-size: 16px; font-weight: 700; margin: 20px 0 10px; }
  .legal-section p { color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.8; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .legal-section ul { color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.8; padding-left: 24px; margin-bottom: 12px; }
  .legal-section ul li { margin-bottom: 6px; }
  .legal-table { width: 100%; border-collapse: collapse; margin: 16px 0; font-size: 14px; }
  .legal-table th, .legal-table td { border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 10px 14px; text-align: left; }
  .legal-table th { background: var(--bg); font-weight: 600; }
  .legal-table td { color: var(--text-secondary); }
  code { background: var(--bg); padding: 2px 6px; border-radius: 3px; font-size: 13px; }
</style>
